"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/522217","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-06-06","<p>The most recent proven reoffending bulletin can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/proven-reoffending-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/proven-reoffending-statistics</a>. A full report with data going back to 2003 can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/519648/proven-reoffending-July-2013-June-2014.xlsx" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/519648/proven-reoffending-July-2013-June-2014.xlsx</a></p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2016-06-06T15:24:36.623Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/522217/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/522217/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/522217/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-05-26","Reoffenders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the reoffending rates are for offenders who have had a conviction (a) under and (b) over 12 months in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Nicholas Brown","Newcastle upon Tyne East","Mr Nicholas Brown","38893"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/522218","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-06-06","<p>Cohorts were established from 1 October 2015 and there will be a 26 month delay before the first Payment by Results payment to allow for robust measurement, cases to clear courts, and analysis of the data. We have therefore not made any payments through Payment by Results to Community Rehabilitation Companies (CRCs).</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2016-06-06T15:52:45.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/522218/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/522218/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/522218/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-05-26","Community Rehabilitation Companies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how much has been paid from the public purse to community rehabilitation companies under the payments-by-results arrangement.","false","Biography information for Mr Nicholas Brown","Newcastle upon Tyne East","Mr Nicholas Brown","38884"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/522219","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-06-08","<p>The information requested could be only obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2016-06-08T15:33:57.627Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/522219/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/522219/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/522219/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-05-26","Probation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many offenders on probation have been (a) classified in each risk category, (b) moved up a risk category and (c) moved down a risk category in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Nicholas Brown","Newcastle upon Tyne East","Mr Nicholas Brown","38881"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/522220","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-06-08","<p>We assess the performance of the National Probation Service and 21 Community Rehabilitation Companies (CRCs) through a range of service levels and, for CRCs, through a robust contract management and assurance process. Performance information against these service levels is published quarterly. The most recent statistics were published on 28 April and can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/community-performance-quarterly-management-information-update-to-december-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/community-performance-quarterly-management-information-update-to-december-2015</a>. Cohorts were established from 1 October 2015 and there will be a 26 month delay to allow for robust measurement over a sustained period, cases to clear courts, and analysis of the data. We will, therefore, be unable to assess whether the reforms are reducing reoffending until December 2017.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2016-06-08T15:14:17.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/522220/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/522220/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/522220/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-05-26","Probation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what assessment he has made of the effect of his policies on transforming rehabilitation on the performance of the Probation Service.","false","Biography information for Mr Nicholas Brown","Newcastle upon Tyne East","Mr Nicholas Brown","38883"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/522221","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-06-08","<p>We are confident our reforms to probation services are being successfully implemented but are not complacent and are working to improve the issues identified in this report. The National Offender Management Service have developed an action plan and we are addressing the Chief Inspector's recommendations.</p><p> </p><p>We continue to closely monitor and robustly manage providers to make sure they fulfil their contractual commitments to maintain service delivery, reduce reoffending, protect the public and provide value for money to the taxpayer and will continue to support probation staff to deliver these important changes.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2016-06-08T15:17:29.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/522221/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/522221/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/522221/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-05-26","Probation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what response he has made to HM Inspectorate of Probation's Transforming Rehabilitation, Early Implementation 5 report, published in May 2016.","false","Biography information for Mr Nicholas Brown","Newcastle upon Tyne East","Mr Nicholas Brown","38911"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/522222","Northern Ireland Office","false","2016-06-09","<p>I refer the hon Member to the Prime Minister's response of 25 May 2016. This information is not collated centrally by the Department.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace",,"2016-06-09T14:39:38.873Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/522222/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/522222/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/522222/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2016-05-26","Northern Ireland Office: UK Membership of EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, pursuant to the Answer of 25 May 2016 to Question 37198, how many of the leaflets entitled Why the Government believes that voting to remain in the European Union is the best decision for the UK have been returned to her Department; and what the postage cost to the Government has been of such returns.","true","Biography information for Tom Pursglove","Corby","Tom Pursglove","38777"
