"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521143","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-06-02","<p>Since the withdrawal of the Nimrod MR2 in March 2010, we have drawn on other military assets, including Type 23 Frigates, submarines and Merlin Anti-Submarine Warfare helicopters and, where appropriate and possible, assistance from allies. We will continue the present practice of issuing requests to allies to provide Maritime Patrol Aircraft when there is an operational need to do so.</p><p>Our allies are well aware of the value of such reciprocal support and there are also many instances of the UK providing support to others. Examples include Quick Reaction Alert aircraft for Baltic Air Policing and the integration of HMS KENT into a French carrier group deployment to the Gulf last year</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","38258","2016-06-02T11:17:15.077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521143/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521143/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521143/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-05-24","Maritime Patrol Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what discussions he has had with which of his international counterparts on the provision of maritime patrol aircraft for use in the UK in advance of the delivery of the P8 aircraft.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","38261"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521144","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-05-26","<p>The UK is concerned about tensions in the South China Sea and the effect that these could have on regional peace and security and global prosperity. We have every interest in maintaining regional stability, respect for freedom of navigation and freedom of overflight. We call on all parties to refrain from activity likely to raise tensions, including land reclamation, construction and militarisation. We urge all parties to exercise restraint and behave responsibly, employing dialogue and diplomacy rather than force or coercion.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2016-05-26T15:29:09.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521144/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521144/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521144/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-05-24","South China Sea","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of the potential security implications of China's naval expansion into the South China Sea; and what steps his Department is taking in response to such expansion.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","38378"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521145","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-06-02","<p>The UK is supporting UNDP led efforts to urgently re-build the capacity of Yemen's national demining institutions and support mapping and clearance operations to reduce the physical and social-economic impact of mines and explosive remnants of war on people and communities. The UK is contributing £1.05 million for this work in 2016 through the Conflict Stability and Security Fund. This is part of the UK’s wider efforts to help address Yemen's urgent humanitarian needs and contribute to effective stabilisation.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-06-02T12:47:46.437Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521145/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521145/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521145/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-05-24","Yemen: Bomb Disposal","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if the Government will produce resources, equipment, personnel and training to Yemeni organisations to assist in the de-mining of areas affected by the use of cluster munitions.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","38339"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521146","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-05-26","<p>Our electronic records show that since 1999 no licences have been granted to Saudi Arabia or Yemen for cluster bombs.</p><p>Paper records prior to 1999 can only be searched at disproportionate cost.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-05-26T15:35:04.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521146/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521146/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521146/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-05-24","Cluster Munitions: Exports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, whether any cluster bombs have been exported under licence from the UK to Saudi Arabia or Yemen since 1989.","false","Biography information for Neil Coyle","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Neil Coyle","38337"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521147","Department for Education","false","2016-06-02","<p>The conditions of grant for the pupil premium make clear that its purpose is to raise the attainment of disadvantaged pupils. School leaders are best placed to decide how to spend the pupil premium in line with this policy and the needs of their pupils.</p><p>It is for schools to commission pupil premium reviews and act upon the recommendations. The recommendations should inform their development of an improved strategy for raising the achievement of disadvantaged pupils and spending their pupil premium funding.</p><p>The Department has not seen the pupil premium report which Ofsted asked the school to commission. However, having reviewed the Ofsted report, and information from the school’s auditors, we have not identified any grounds for further action.</p><p>The Hon. Member, Andrew Gwynne, has met the Regional Schools Commissioner for Lancashire and West Yorkshire, Vicky Beer, on a number of occasions to discuss his concerns about Audenshaw School Academy Trust and contact is ongoing.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","38197 ; 38199 ; 38200 ; 38201","2016-06-02T14:10:51.947Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521147/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521147/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521147/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-05-24","Audenshaw School","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 23 May 2016 to Question 37377, if she will place in the Library a copy of the report commissioned by Audenshaw School as part of an Ofsted requirement into the use of pupil premium money at that school.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","38198"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521148","Department for Education","false","2016-06-02","<p>The conditions of grant for the pupil premium make clear that its purpose is to raise the attainment of disadvantaged pupils. School leaders are best placed to decide how to spend the pupil premium in line with this policy and the needs of their pupils.</p><p>It is for schools to commission pupil premium reviews and act upon the recommendations. The recommendations should inform their development of an improved strategy for raising the achievement of disadvantaged pupils and spending their pupil premium funding.</p><p>The Department has not seen the pupil premium report which Ofsted asked the school to commission. However, having reviewed the Ofsted report, and information from the school’s auditors, we have not identified any grounds for further action.</p><p>The Hon. Member, Andrew Gwynne, has met the Regional Schools Commissioner for Lancashire and West Yorkshire, Vicky Beer, on a number of occasions to discuss his concerns about Audenshaw School Academy Trust and contact is ongoing.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","38197 ; 38198 ; 38200 ; 38201","2016-06-02T14:10:52.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521148/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521148/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521148/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-05-24","Audenshaw School","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 23 May 2016 to Question 37377, if she will meet with the hon. Member for Denton and Reddish to discuss his concerns about Audenshaw School.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","38199"
