"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521153","Department for Education","false","2016-06-06","<p>We are currently considering the School Teachers’ Review Body’s report, its publication and the publication of the draft School Teachers’ Pay and Conditions Document.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2016-06-06T10:58:15.58Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521153/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521153/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521153/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-05-24","Teachers: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, when she plans to respond to the School Teachers' Review Body report on teachers' pay from September 2016; and when she plans to publish the draft 2016 School Teachers' Pay and Conditions document for consultation and information.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","38401"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521154","Department for Education","false","2016-06-15","<p>The Department for Education sets a requirement that young people who do not achieve a GCSE grade C in English or mathematics by age 16 should continue the study of these subjects. This requirement applies only to 16-19 study programmes funded by the Education Funding Agency (EFA) and is set out in a funding condition for schools and colleges which receive EFA funding. The requirement would therefore apply to any member of the armed forces undertaking EFA-funded 16-19 programmes. It would not apply to requirements for training provided and funded by the armed forces, which are a matter for the Ministry of Defence.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2016-06-15T14:17:27.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521154/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521154/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521154/answer","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521154/answer/previousversion/2037","Biography information for Nick Gibb","60","Education","Education","2016-05-24","Armed Forces: GCSE","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether armed forces trainees are included in the policy of ensuring that by 2020 young people who do not achieve A* to C passes in English and mathematics GCSEs at age 16 resit their exams a year later.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","38405"
